00:28:17.920 --> 00:28:20.894
companies, they have this
kind of general theory

00:28:20.894 --> 00:28:23.310
that whatever knowledge they're
putting out into the world

00:28:23.310 --> 00:28:25.750
somehow makes it better.

00:28:25.750 --> 00:28:28.110
In the case of
Facebook, they believe

00:28:28.110 --> 00:28:31.910
that people sharing information
and pictures of their family

00:28:31.910 --> 00:28:34.502
would create more
connections between people.

00:28:34.502 --> 00:28:35.710
People would develop empathy.

00:28:38.260 --> 00:28:41.320
We would be a more bipartisan
nation, things like this.

00:28:41.320 --> 00:28:45.530
When it came to Twitter,
the founders of Twitter

00:28:45.530 --> 00:28:48.450
told me that it started out
as kind of like an information

00:28:48.450 --> 00:28:52.780
broadcasting service, where one
of the founders was on a BART.

00:28:52.780 --> 00:28:54.300
And if he experienced
an earthquake,

00:28:54.300 --> 00:28:58.730
he would want to let everyone
know that he was OK, right?

00:28:58.730 --> 00:29:00.760
So when I say
information, it's tackled

00:29:00.760 --> 00:29:06.270
like one product at a time,
and it's one bill at a time.

00:29:06.270 --> 00:29:11.280
So the idea of cities building
very dense and tall cities,

00:29:11.280 --> 00:29:14.920
the idea is that you can invite
people of all income brackets

00:29:14.920 --> 00:29:15.900
into the same area.

00:29:15.900 --> 00:29:19.250
They can enjoy the same
schools and job opportunities.

00:29:19.250 --> 00:29:22.000
And you can invite smart people
from all over the country

00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:24.275
to work in the most
productive companies.

00:29:27.410 --> 00:29:29.790
I mean, I'm using knowledge
kind of writ large,

00:29:29.790 --> 00:29:32.314
but it's tackled one policy,
one product at a time.

00:29:32.314 --> 00:29:34.105
I don't know if that
answers your question.

