00:34:45.130 --> 00:34:47.600
AUDIENCE: You mentioned
you based a lot of this

00:34:47.600 --> 00:34:50.659
on this survey that you did.

00:34:50.659 --> 00:34:54.380
Now was there controls?

00:34:54.380 --> 00:34:56.880
Because that's somewhat of
self-selection as to who

00:34:56.880 --> 00:34:58.250
returns the survey.

00:34:58.250 --> 00:35:00.050
Perhaps it was just
all the Libertarians.

00:35:00.050 --> 00:35:01.500
Perhaps it was all Democrats.

00:35:01.500 --> 00:35:03.690
How did you do
controls for that?

00:35:03.690 --> 00:35:07.340
GREGORY FERENSTEIN: Well, so you
can't do controls in a survey.

00:35:07.340 --> 00:35:08.950
All surveys-- all
political opinion

00:35:08.950 --> 00:35:11.491
surveys-- unless you like strap
someone down and torture them

00:35:11.491 --> 00:35:14.970
until they answer questions,
are, by definition, voluntary.

00:35:14.970 --> 00:35:19.220
What you hope is that you get a
broad enough sample of people,

00:35:19.220 --> 00:35:22.669
and that the people who answer
your question-- I guess what

00:35:22.669 --> 00:35:25.210
you hope is that the reason why
someone answers your question

00:35:25.210 --> 00:35:28.220
is independent of their
political ideology.

00:35:28.220 --> 00:35:31.250
So if you believe that if you're
more Libertarian or culturally

00:35:31.250 --> 00:35:34.730
conservative you're more
likely to answer any opinion

00:35:34.730 --> 00:35:36.830
poll, than yes, it's a problem.

00:35:39.480 --> 00:35:42.220
Just speaking kind of broadly
about public opinion polling--

00:35:42.220 --> 00:35:44.840
political opinion
polling-- I think

00:35:44.840 --> 00:35:46.854
some surveys show
that conservatives

00:35:46.854 --> 00:35:48.520
are popular in some
states, and liberals

00:35:48.520 --> 00:35:49.820
are popular in other states.

00:35:49.820 --> 00:35:52.290
So just answering a
survey seems to be

00:35:52.290 --> 00:35:55.680
independent of your
political ideology.

00:35:55.680 --> 00:35:57.430
I tried to sample
enough founders.

00:35:57.430 --> 00:35:59.342
I sampled about 144.

00:35:59.342 --> 00:36:01.300
The margin of error was
about plus or minus 7%.

