00:36:26.930 --> 00:36:29.250
in terms of like kind
of the Bernie Sanders

00:36:29.250 --> 00:36:31.412
camp of the Democratic
Party, I guess,

00:36:31.412 --> 00:36:33.120
and the people who
seem to be looking out

00:36:33.120 --> 00:36:34.850
for the interest of
working class people

00:36:34.850 --> 00:36:36.530
and the more
meritocratic side, that

00:36:36.530 --> 00:36:40.060
seems to just want
to empower people

00:36:40.060 --> 00:36:45.690
but may not look out for people
who are like super motivated

00:36:45.690 --> 00:36:48.772
and driven to capitalize
on those opportunities?

00:36:48.772 --> 00:36:50.980
GREGORY FERENSTEIN: So that's
a really good question.

00:36:50.980 --> 00:36:51.810
I'm glad you asked it.

00:36:51.810 --> 00:36:54.060
I'm going to give it a little
bit of a lengthy answer.

00:36:54.060 --> 00:36:56.250
But I'll try to keep it short.

00:36:56.250 --> 00:37:01.147
So I once thought this ideology
was pretty tied to income.

00:37:01.147 --> 00:37:03.480
If you made a lot of money
and you were highly educated,

00:37:03.480 --> 00:37:04.854
you tended to
believe this thing.

00:37:04.854 --> 00:37:06.630
I was wrong.

00:37:06.630 --> 00:37:11.460
I started doing surveys-- thanks
to the Google Surveys team

00:37:11.460 --> 00:37:12.200
actually.

00:37:12.200 --> 00:37:17.250
They're great-- of gig economy
workers in San Francisco.

00:37:17.250 --> 00:37:19.560
I was able to filter
people who worked for Uber

00:37:19.560 --> 00:37:22.330
and Lyft an InstaCart
and TaskRabbit.

00:37:22.330 --> 00:37:25.230
Gig economy workers
have a political profile

00:37:25.230 --> 00:37:28.770
much closer to tech workers,
than people who tell me they're

00:37:28.770 --> 00:37:30.500
in a union.

00:37:30.500 --> 00:37:31.690
This makes sense.

00:37:31.690 --> 00:37:34.320
They have a more
entrepreneurial lifestyle.

00:37:34.320 --> 00:37:38.250
They are bigger fans of
high-skilled immigrants

00:37:38.250 --> 00:37:41.740
like tech workers, because
high-skilled immigrants

00:37:41.740 --> 00:37:44.770
help create the products
that give them a job.

00:37:44.770 --> 00:37:46.890
On presidential
candidates, they're

00:37:46.890 --> 00:37:50.870
bigger fans of Hillary Clinton
than Bernie Sanders, who

00:37:50.870 --> 00:37:54.560
potentially could be the
person to regulate technology,

00:37:54.560 --> 00:37:58.810
if he ever got to be president,
more so than Clinton.

00:37:58.810 --> 00:38:01.480
Because they live an
entrepreneurial existence,

00:38:01.480 --> 00:38:03.400
they're more like tech
workers, and they need

00:38:03.400 --> 00:38:04.868
a similar role for government.

00:38:07.490 --> 00:38:09.130
It turns out that
this has happened

00:38:09.130 --> 00:38:11.350
before in Democratic history.

00:38:11.350 --> 00:38:13.310
The original
progressives, people

00:38:13.310 --> 00:38:15.020
who called themselves
progressives

00:38:15.020 --> 00:38:22.500
in the Democratic Party, go
all the way back to 1840.

00:38:22.500 --> 00:38:24.570
Originally, the Democratic
Party as a whole

00:38:24.570 --> 00:38:25.854
was against free trade.

00:38:25.854 --> 00:38:28.270
This was before the United
States had much of a free trade

00:38:28.270 --> 00:38:30.484
agreement at all.

00:38:30.484 --> 00:38:32.900
And when the government tried
to introduce more free trade

00:38:32.900 --> 00:38:37.230
principles, the bill failed.

00:38:37.230 --> 00:38:39.770
When the new high-tech
industry of the time

00:38:39.770 --> 00:38:43.820
in the 1840s, the railroads,
partnered with low-skilled farm

00:38:43.820 --> 00:38:47.290
workers, who wanted to
sell their goods abroad,

00:38:47.290 --> 00:38:49.400
they banded together a
high-skilled industry

00:38:49.400 --> 00:38:52.360
and a low-skilled industry
to fundamentally change

00:38:52.360 --> 00:38:57.330
America's economic stance
to the rest of the world.

00:38:57.330 --> 00:39:01.220
This is happening, I
believe, 150 years later,

00:39:01.220 --> 00:39:02.820
with tech workers
and gig economy

00:39:02.820 --> 00:39:07.044
workers, the same alliance
just different policies.

00:39:10.190 --> 00:39:12.180
That was a long answer.

00:39:12.180 --> 00:39:13.860
Thank you.

00:39:13.860 --> 00:39:20.860
AUDIENCE: I'm wondering about
